post_text: Patriot Day tomorrow. Let us not forget.
shared_text:
TeacherGoals
September 10 at 8:14 PM ·

Let us not forget...

On this night 19 years ago 246 people went to sleep in preparation for their morning flights. 2,606 people went to sleep in preparation for work in the morning. 343 firefighters went to sleep in preparation for their morning shift. 60 police officers went to sleep in preparation for morning patrol. 8 paramedics went to sleep in preparation for the morning shift of saving lives. None of them saw past 10:00 a.m. Sept 11, 2001.

In one single moment life can change forever. Tonight as you go to sleep in preparation for your life tomorrow, kiss the ones you love, snuggle a little tighter, and never take one second of your life for granted.

#wewillneverforget 🇺🇸

post_text: Did you know that Labor Day became a federal holiday more than 125 years ago? On June 28, 1894, Congress passed an act making the first Monday in September of each year a legal holiday in the District of Columbia and the territories. Find out more at https://www.dol.gov/general/laborday/history.

post_text: Education Code 60119 requires the Board to conduct an annual public hearing to determine the sufficiency of District Textbooks and instructional materials. At the hearing, the Board must determine by resolution whether each District student has or will have before the end of that fiscal year sufficient textbooks and /or instructional materials. This notice serves to inform the public that Lake Elementary School District will be holding a public hearing on September 15, 2020 at 6:00 p.m. to determine sufficiency of instructional materials for students in the District for the 2020-21 school year.

shared_text:
Kyle Goings
July 18 at 9:43 AM ·

With the start of school getting closer I wanted to try & make some sense of the case #'s for Glenn County, to see how close we are to getting off "the list." I used the daily info Glenn Co HHSA shares to find any patterns. Here are the graphs I made. #5 & 6 are important because they're related to the state's "monitoring guidelines." I'm sure the numbers aren't perfect, but it does look like we might be doing a little better. Hope these help.

We hope you have fun with this resource! https://characterlab.org/

post_text: It is with a heavy heart that we share the passing of a Lake Panther mom, Fatima Ibanez. Fatima and her husband, Zenaido, were visiting family in Mexico when she passed away in her sleep. Our hearts go out to the children, Anahi and Danny, 12th grade and 8th grade, respectively. For those who have been part of the Lake Family for the past five years, you will recall we lost their oldest daughter, Jacqueline, to kidney failure when she was in the 8th grade at Lake. This GoFundMe page has been created to help the family with unexpected funeral costs. Our Lake Family appreciates your support of one of our own. https://www.gofundme.com/f/fatima-funeral-expenses

If you're a parent or teacher struggling with distance learning, consider adding some mindfulness and meditation to your school day. There are some easy activities to get your started and apps you can use for free on this post... https://bit.ly/2yRUfzJ

#mindfulness #meditation #anxiety #mentalhealth #distancelearning #children #students #teachers #parenting

post_text: Wise words.
shared_text:
Anxiety & I
February 18 at 12:37 PM ·

"Today was a Difficult Day," said Pooh.

There was a pause.

"Do you want to talk about it?" asked Piglet.

"No," said Pooh after a bit. "No, I don't think I do."

"That's okay," said Piglet, and he came and sat beside his friend.

"What are you doing?" asked Pooh.

"Nothing, really," said Piglet. "Only, I know what Difficult Days are like. I quite often don't feel like talking about it on my Difficult Days either.

"But goodness," continued Piglet, "Difficult Days are so much easier when you know you've got someone there for you. And I'll always be here for you, Pooh."

And as Pooh sat there, working through in his head his Difficult Day, while the solid, reliable Piglet sat next to him quietly, swinging his little legs...he thought that his best friend had never been more right."
A.A. Milne

Sending thoughts to those having a Difficult Day today and hope you have your own Piglet to sit beside you 🧡

post_text: Hello Monday! This might be something neat to add to your daily routines on Tuesdays and Fridays at 10:00 am. Check out the link to her weather forecast and the opportunity for students to ask questions. #golakepanthers
shared_text:
Meteorologist Mallory Brooke
March 20 at 2:05 PM ·

Hey everyone! While I know teachers have been working tirelessly around the clock getting curriculums set for distance learning (go teachers! 🙌), I wanted to offer up some weather discussion time for the kiddos during the week. On Tuesday's & Friday's, I'll be initiating a livestream that's all weather focused. We'll go through the day's weather, talk about the upcoming weather, and then I want to take questions from your kids! Hoping that this gives them a moment to break from "school", but still providing some educational fun and social time.

Join me 10:00am every Tuesday and Friday, until we're back in the actual classroom. Please share around your community and beyond!

High school members of the local SWAT (Students Working Against Tobacco) Team will be on campus visiting with students in grades 5-8 regarding the harmful effects of tobacco.

The annual Kindergarten Thanksgiving Program & Feast will take place at 11:00 a.m. Parents, get those cameras ready!

post_text:
As we embark on the last week of October, we’re dedicating this week to Leadership’s Kindness Campaign by giving sincere compliments.

Like someone’s shirt? Tell them.

Like their haircut? Tell them.

Did a classmate perform well in the classroom on an assignment? Congratulate them.

Monday’s challenge is to give two sincere compliments today. Not sure what to say? Please take a compliment from the list below.

#kindnessmatters #glennlearns #golakepanthers
